SIMPLE: seasonal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seasonal
<hw>Sea"son*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to the seasons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Occurring or being used in a specific season;
<as>as, <ex>seasonal</ex> items for sale</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Seasonal dimorphism</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the
condition of having two distinct varieties which appear at different
seasons, as certain species of butterflies in which the spring brood
differs from the summer or autumnal brood.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>seasonal affective disorder</ent>⟦br⟧
